               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1225" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1225" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1225" type="surname" value="PERRY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1225" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PERRY</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Ship and Sailor ale-house, in Church-street, Greenwich. I lost several tools—I had left home for a fortnight in Fe<lb></lb>bruary, and in my absence they were taken—I had used them the day before I left—the prisoner has frequently used my tap-room—I did not authorise him to pawn any of these articles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1226" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1226" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1226" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1226" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD BOLTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an apprentice to Mr. Harber, a pawnbroker, at Greenwhich. On the 12th of February a saw and plane were pawned at master's by the prisoner—I recollect him—1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. was advanced for the two—I have the ticket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1227" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1227" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1227" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker at Greenwhich. On Satur<lb></lb>day evening, the prisoner came with this plane, which he wanted 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on—I asked him whose it was—he said his father's—I said I should like to see his father; and on the Monday he came and said, "Mr. Williams, my father says he is unable to come, and unless you advance the money or restore the plane, he shall seek further redress"—I was taken off my guard, and lent him the 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. <hi rend="smallCaps">THOMAS LARKIN</hi>. I apprehended the prisoner at his mother's house, in Greenwhich, last Thursday—I told him the charge—he denied it, and said he knew nothing about the tools.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced sworn to</hi>.) <hi rend="smallCaps">JAMES WILD</hi>. I am a policeman. I produce a certificate of the pri<lb></lb>soner's former condviction, which I got from Mr. Straight's office—I was present at Maidstone when the prisoner was tried and convicted there in March, 1834 (<hi rend="italic">read</hi>). <hi rend="largeCaps">
